/*! jxl.js (niutech/jxl.js multithread) — decoder WASM rebuilt from libjxl v0.12.0 tools/wasm_demo
   (emscripten 6.0.2, scalar + simd128 variants, pthreads; no separate .worker.js — workers bootstrap
   from the main script; module factory is JxlDecoderModule). Decoder rebuild notes: configure with
   -DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS=OFF (else it dlopens .so side modules at runtime), drop "--closure 1" from
   JXL_WASM_SITE_LINK_FLAGS unless Java is installed, build the simd variant with -msimd128 in
   C/CXX/linker flags and sed its emitted js to fetch "jxl_decoder_simd.wasm", and patch
   jxl_decoder.cc to call JxlDecoderSetCms(dec, *JxlGetDefaultCms()) after SetParallelRunner —
   without it HDR->SDR tone mapping fails (upstream wasm_demo bug). Local patches to this file,
   re-apply if re-vendoring:
   1. MutationObserver also watches img src attribute changes, so decoding triggers when a page swaps src on an existing <img> (DistanceVsEffort.js).
   2. On end-of-stream, keep pumping _jxlProcessInput with 0 new bytes until the decoder reports done instead of destroying it immediately — otherwise files that arrive in a single network read (< ~64KB) lose the race against the decoder's worker threads and only the blurry 1/8-res progressive DC preview is ever painted.
   3. Share a single WASM module across all images (upstream instantiated a new module + memory + worker pool per image, which exhausts address space on gallery pages) and serialize decodes through a queue — concurrent instances on one module deadlock the main thread contending for the pthread pool. Also skip CacheStorage reads/writes for data: URIs, which the Cache API rejects.
   4. Optional HDR output path: a page can set window.jxl = { preferHdr: true } before this script; on HDR displays (dynamic-range: high) in Chromium browsers, images are then decoded via _jxlDecompress into a 16-bit PNG with a cICP chunk (Rec.2100 PQ/HLG preserved) instead of the tone-mapped SDR canvas->JPEG path, so they render in true HDR. Whole-file decode (no progressive preview), drops alpha, skips CacheStorage. forceHdr: true bypasses the display/browser gate (testing). */
